          <tr>
            <td> <font face="Verdana">
            <h3>Welcome to ExPrimer</h3>
            </font> <font face="Verdana" size="2">ExPrimer is a web
based computer program to design primers from
exon-exon junctions of a specified gene transcript. The tool suggests
the optimum pair(s) of primers of which the right (reverse) primer
always represents the exon-exon junction of the mRNA. The results page
lists all other primer pairs considered along with the computed scores
for various primer-parameters. ExPrimer has an option to interface with
NCBI BLASTn program to evaluate sequence specificity of the primers.
The tool can have applications in many areas of molecular biology
research that involve RT-PCR, expression profiling of splice variants
etc. For more information please refer to <a
 href="http://exprimer.ibab.ac.in/exprimer_html/userguide.html">user-guide</a>.
            </font> </td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
      <center><img src="exprimer_files/exprimer.jpg"></center>
      </td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>
